The '''London Conference on the Illegal Wildlife Trade''' was an international conference held on 12–13 February 2014 in [[London]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/topical-events/illegal-wildlife-trade-2014 |title=London Conference on the Illegal Wildlife Trade 2014 |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=February 2014 |website= |publisher=[[gov.uk]] |accessdate=13 February 2014}}</ref> A declaration to protect wildlife was signed by 46 countries and 11 international organizations. The declaration calls for increasing enforcement of laws against poaching, reducing demand for wildlife products, and the "sustainable utilization" of wildlife.<ref>By Arancha Gonzalez in the Wall Street Journal on March 3, 2014.</ref>
