==Adaptations==

The Montreal-based RustWerk ReFinery adapted the book in 2016 as ''Louis Riel: A Comic-Strip Stage Play''.  The bilingual play uses black-and-white cut-out puppets, live actors, and shadow imagery.{{sfn|Little|2016}}

